Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%grams}(quartered larger pieces).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water, lower heat to medium and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

When the chicken is golden, stir in the @korma curry paste{1%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @creme fraiche{110%grams}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

> Double sugar for 4p.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, place the @naan{2} onto a lined #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little @water{to taste} then pop into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @honey{1%sachet} to the pan. Stir until incorporated, ~{30%seconds}.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and sugar if needed.

Divide your chicken korma between the naans.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until golden and toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @tomato{2}(into 1cm chunks).

Roughly chop the @chives{5%grams}.

In a medium #bowl{}, mix the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} with a drizzle of oil, salt, pepper and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

> Double sugar for 4p.

Toss the tomato and chives through the dressing.

When the potatoes are cooked and drained, stir through the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use less chilli flakes if you don't like spice—or if you're cooking for kids. Double butter for 4p.

Plate up your loaded chicken korma naans.

Serve the buttery chilli potatoes alongside.

To finish, spoon the tomato salsa over the naan.